></div></section><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is Remote Patient Monitoring (RPM)?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Remote Patient Monitoring (RPM) is a way for healthcare providers to track patient health data (like blood pressure, glucose, weight, or recovery progress) between visits. Using connected health trackers and apps, providers can deliver continuous care while patients stay at home."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How can RPM help my practice generate revenue?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Clinics can offer RPM as a subscription care plan, charging patients monthly or otherwise for ongoing monitoring. For chronic conditions or post-surgical care, these plans create predictable recurring revenue while improving patient outcomes."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What conditions can be monitored with RPM?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Our system supports 70+ health trackers, enabling setup of plans covering chronic diseases like diabetes, hypertension, hypertension, COPD, skin conditions etc. as well as short-term monitoring needs such as post-surgery recovery."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do I need a separate system for RPM?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No. Our Remote Monitoring feature is fully integrated with your EHR, appointments, billing, and consultations. This means no extra logins or disconnected workflows — everything stays in your Virtual Practice."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does RPM improve patient engagement?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Patients can log data through their mobile app or connect popular devices like blood pressure monitors and wearables. This keeps them actively involved in their care, while providers receive alerts and can step in before issues escalate."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is Remote Patient Monitoring secure and compliant?","acceptedAnswer":